The Union government will fulfil all promises made in the A.P. Reorganisation Act during bifurcation of the State, Union Minister of Law and Justice D.V. Sadananda Gowda said on Friday.Addressing the media at Kadapa State guest house, the Minister said the issue of release of Krishna water to Rayalaseema was pending before the Truibunal and necessary steps would be taken in accordance with the verdict to be pronounced. The BJP had assured release of 250 tmcft of Krishna water to Rayalaseema in its election manifesto.Kadapa district has several cement factories and there was need for power projects in the district, Mr. Sadananda Gowda said.Mr. Gowda, who is on a tour of Kadapa district for the second day, said his tour was in tune with Prime Minister Narendra Modiâ€™s fiat to Union Ministers to tour two Parliamentary constituencies every month, elicit public opinion and gauge to what extent the government schemes reached the common man.